{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EPj2eq9ZXcSkLuR91nMAZL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the replica set `rs0` is already initialized. Now I need to:\n\n1. Generate certificates using openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Create a Kubernetes Secret with the certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to mount the secret and add TLS flags\n4. Verify TLS works and plain connections fail\n\nLet me check what SANs I need. The MongoDB pods will have DNS names like:\n- mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n- mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n- mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n- mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\n\nI need to generate a CA certificate, then create server and client certificates with all the appropriate SANs. For MongoDB's TLS setup, the server.pem file combines the server certificate and private key, while client.pem does the same for the client, and ca.crt holds just the CA certificate. Let me use the openssl-toolbox to create these.\n\nFor the MongoDB configuration, I'll need to set `--tlsMode requireTLS` and point to the server.pem and ca.crt files. Since we're restarting the pods with TLS enabled, I need to be careful about how the replica set handles the transition—enabling TLS in \"allow\" mode first before switching to \"require\" mode would normally be safer, but since the pods are restarting anyway, I should ensure the replica set can reinitialize properly with TLS from the start.\n\nMy plan is to generate the certificates using an openssl container, store them in a Kubernetes Secret, mount that Secret in the StatefulSet, and add the TLS arguments to the mongod command. The tricky part is handling the rolling update—if mongo-rs-0 starts with TLS required before the other replicas, they won't be able to communicate. Since this is an ephemeral cluster, I can just reinitialize the replica set cleanly with TLS enabled across all members.\n\nI'll start by generating the server certificates with the proper DNS names for all three pods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":343,"cache_read_input_tokens":30348,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":343},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"860f0b88-8ae5-4485-9d76-fc1ddc1d3079","uuid":"b5083e4b-9444-442f-b32e-5b3f48e49685","request_id":"req_011CcLLSMBdnzNb9qmKs3EU5"}
